<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">November 4, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-november-4-2024/"><img class="wp-image-245261 size-thumbnail aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/AdobeStock_287251658-150x150.jpeg" alt="ghostwriter" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.vulture.com/article/celebrity-novels-ghostwriting.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Who’s really writing those celebrity novels</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">?</span></li>
 	<li><a href="https://electricliterature.com/mosab-abu-tohas-poetry-is-a-heart-wrenching-account-of-life-in-gaza-and-here-is-what-he-wants-you-to-know/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">What poet Mosab Abu Toha wants you to know about life in Gaza</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/books/second-read/dorothy-parker-and-the-art-of-the-literary-takedown" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Dorothy Parker as a master of the literary takedown</span></a></li>
</ul>
